That&#39;s why I wish someone would mass-produce these boxes.  If we got enough of them out there being used, it would eventually become obvious the voices are not fake. 

Of all my friends and family I&#39;ve told about this thing, only two believe me -- one is my best friend who is very open to paranormal stuff, and the other is my mother, who didn&#39;t believe any of it until she had her mother come through and answer questions about her childhood dog.  Then, even though she didn&#39;t want to, she was forced to believe. She still doesn&#39;t like to talk about it.

I dare anyone to turn this thing on, give it an honest open-minded try, and not have anything happen.  Hell, I turned on my new little 12-587 at the vet&#39;s office Friday while I was waiting, just to see what would happen, and it said my name.  Then the vet came in.  It makes me wonder if there&#39;s a lot of residual emotional energy in a vet&#39;s office, what with animals dying and making owners cry and whatnot.

Jill  





